---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navigation from '../components/Navigation.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="About - Paper Lanterns" 
  description="Learn about Paper Lanterns, a curated digital archive preserving historically significant letters and speeches for future generations."
>
  <Navigation />
  
  <main class="about-container">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="about-header">
        <h1 class="about-title">About Paper Lanterns</h1>
        <p class="about-subtitle">
          Preserving the intimate conversations and powerful orations that shaped our world
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="about-content">
        <section class="mission-section">
          <h2 class="section-title">Our Mission</h2>
          <div class="section-content">
            <p>
              Before the age of instant communication, every written word carried weight. Letters were deliberate, 
              speeches were crafted with care, and each sentence was chosen with intention. These documents reveal 
              not just historical facts, but the human experiences behind them—the hopes, fears, loves, and dreams 
              of those who came before us.
            </p>
            <p>
              Voice from time is dedicated to preserving and presenting these remarkable documents as they deserve 
              to be seen: as works of art, windows into the soul, and bridges across time. We believe that in an 
              age of fleeting messages, these enduring words remind us of the power of thoughtful communication.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="curation-section">
          <h2 class="section-title">Curation Philosophy</h2>
          <div class="section-content">
            <p>
              Every letter and speech in our collection has been carefully selected based on five key criteria:
            </p>
            <ul class="criteria-list">
              <li>
                <strong>Historical significance</strong> — Documents that shaped culture, politics, science, or human thought
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Emotional resonance</strong> — Letters that reveal universal human experiences and emotions
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Literary quality</strong> — Beautiful, memorable language that demonstrates the art of expression
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Public domain status</strong> — All content is completely free of copyright restrictions
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Authenticity</strong> — Verified historical documents with reliable provenance
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="approach-section">
          <h2 class="section-title">Our Approach</h2>
          <div class="section-content">
            <p>
              We treat each document as a precious artifact, presenting it with the respect and attention it deserves. 
              Our design philosophy emphasizes:
            </p>
            <div class="approach-grid">
              <div class="approach-item">
                <h3>Typography as Art</h3>
                <p>Every letter begins with a beautiful drop cap, and we use premium typography to honor the written word.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="approach-item">
                <h3>Breathing Room</h3>
                <p>Generous whitespace allows readers to focus completely on the text without distraction.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="approach-item">
                <h3>Historical Context</h3>
                <p>We provide just enough background to understand the circumstances without overwhelming the content.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="approach-item">
                <h3>Accessibility</h3>
                <p>Everyone should be able to experience these remarkable documents, regardless of their capabilities.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="collection-stats">
          <h2 class="section-title">What You'll Find</h2>
          <div class="stats-grid">
            <div class="stat-card">
              <span class="stat-number">150+</span>
              <span class="stat-label">Historical Documents</span>
            </div>
            <div class="stat-card">
              <span class="stat-number">500+</span>
              <span class="stat-label">Years of History</span>
            </div>
            <div class="stat-card">
              <span class="stat-number">12</span>
              <span class="stat-label">Thematic Collections</span>
            </div>
            <div class="stat-card">
              <span class="stat-number">100%</span>
              <span class="stat-label">Public Domain</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="team-section">
          <h2 class="section-title">Behind the Project</h2>
          <div class="section-content">
            <p>
              Voice from time was created by a team of historians, designers, and technologists who share a 
              passion for preserving human expression. We believe that these letters and speeches contain 
              timeless wisdom and beauty that should be accessible to everyone.
            </p>
            <p>
              Our editorial team includes PhD historians who verify the authenticity and provide context for 
              each document. Our design team works to present each letter as beautifully as possible, while 
              our developers ensure the site is fast, accessible, and preserved for future generations.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="contribute-section">
          <h2 class="section-title">Contribute to Our Mission</h2>
          <div class="section-content">
            <p>
              We're always looking for remarkable letters and speeches that meet our curation standards. 
              If you know of a public domain document that deserves preservation and presentation, we'd 
              love to hear from you.
            </p>
            <p>
              We also welcome corrections, additional context, or improved citations for existing content. 
              Our goal is to be the most accurate and comprehensive collection of its kind.
            </p>
            <div class="contact-info">
              <a href="mailto:hello@voicefromtime.com" class="contact-link">
                Get in touch →
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>

      <footer class="about-footer">
        <p>All content on Voice from time is in the public domain and freely available to all.</p>
      </footer>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .about-container {
    padding: 6rem 0 4rem;
    min-height: 100vh;
  }

  .container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 2rem;
  }

  .about-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .about-title {
    font-family: 'EB Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 3rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .about-subtitle {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .about-content {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 4rem;
  }

  .section-title {
    font-family: 'EB Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .section-title::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    bottom: -0.5rem;
    left: 0;
    width: 3rem;
    height: 2px;
    background: var(--accent-primary);
  }

  .section-content {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .section-content p {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .section-content p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .criteria-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .criteria-list li {
    padding: 0.75rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-secondary);
  }

  .criteria-list li:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .criteria-list strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .approach-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .approach-item h3 {
    font-family: 'EB Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .approach-item p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .collection-stats {
    background: var(--bg-accent);
    padding: 3rem;
    border-radius: 12px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .stats-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(150px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .stat-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .stat-number {
    font-family: 'EB Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--accent-primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .stat-label {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .contact-info {
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .contact-link {
    color: var(--accent-primary);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    transition: opacity 0.2s ease;
  }

  .contact-link:hover {
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  .about-footer {
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 4rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-secondary);
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about-container {
      padding: 4rem 0 2rem;
    }

    .container {
      padding: 0 1rem;
    }

    .about-title {
      font-size: 2.5rem;
    }

    .about-content {
      gap: 3rem;
    }

    .section-title {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }

    .section-content {
      font-size: 1rem;
    }

    .approach-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1.5rem;
    }

    .collection-stats {
      padding: 2rem 1rem;
    }

    .stats-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
      gap: 1.5rem;
    }

    .stat-number {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }
  }
</style>